Key Match Events: Trent Alexander-Arnold curled a stunning free-kick to score England's second goal.
Jack Grealish opened the scoring with a cool finish after a lovely flick from Angel Gomes.
Declan Rice scored England's third goal from a cross by Ollie Watkins.
Arttu Hoskonen scored Finland's late consolation goal from a corner.
Pre-Game Insights: Lee Carsley fears losing focus if he talks about a permanent England job.
The match was seen as a return to the tranquil progress of Carsley's first camp in September, following the Wembley defeat against Greece.
Post-Match Reflections: Lee Carsley praised the team's resilience after coming back from 2-0 down.
The match was described as a stroll against a limited Finland team.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Harry Kane scored a last-minute winner in injury time.
